WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:01:14.955 --> 00:01:16.183
Don't know how many times

3
00:01:16.290 --> 00:01:19.123
I've been crossed off the list
and left for dead.

4
00:01:20.594 --> 00:01:23.530
Guess when it first happens
the day you were born...

5
00:01:24.332 --> 00:01:25.560
you're gonna lose count.

6
00:01:31.373 --> 00:01:32.465
So this...

7
00:01:33.975 --> 00:01:35.841
this ain't nothing new.

8
00:10:55.845 --> 00:10:57.403
There are bad days...

9
00:10:59.716 --> 00:11:02.184
and then there are legendary bad days.

10
00:11:04.087 --> 00:11:06.386
This was shaping up to be one of those.

11
00:11:09.093 --> 00:11:11.254
Whole damn planet wanted a piece of me.

12
00:11:13.664 --> 00:11:15.325
Can't stay in the open.

13
00:11:17.902 --> 00:11:19.768
Can't risk another attack.

14
00:11:37.790 --> 00:11:41.226
It's always the punch you don't see
coming that puts you down.

15
00:11:44.997 --> 00:11:46.464
But why didn't I see it?

16
00:11:48.769 --> 00:11:50.396
Of course they were
gonna try to kill me.

17
00:11:51.238 --> 00:11:53.069
Death is what they do for a living.

18
00:11:58.745 --> 00:12:00.577
So the question ain't
"What happened?"

19
00:12:03.685 --> 00:12:04.845
The question is...

20
00:12:06.554 --> 00:12:07.714
"What happened to me?"

21
00:12:30.580 --> 00:12:32.639
You are the Lord Marshal now.

22
00:12:33.984 --> 00:12:35.713
How did they get so close?

23
00:12:40.290 --> 00:12:42.885
How did I let them
blindside me like that?

24
00:12:43.895 --> 00:12:46.557
Threshold!
Take us to the threshold!

25
00:12:47.565 --> 00:12:49.032
Necromongers.

26
00:12:50.401 --> 00:12:52.733
Some wanted to put a crown on my head.

27
00:12:54.873 --> 00:12:57.535
Some wanted to put a noose
around my neck.

28
00:12:59.845 --> 00:13:01.039
Please...

29
00:13:01.914 --> 00:13:03.176
come back to bed.

30
00:13:04.616 --> 00:13:08.052
Every Lord Marshal was supposed
to take some big oath...

31
00:13:09.656 --> 00:13:13.956
one that I never really got around to.

32
00:13:15.895 --> 00:13:17.954
You could say it created
a little friction...

33
00:13:19.999 --> 00:13:22.491
and more than a few assassins.

34
00:13:25.539 --> 00:13:26.904
I needed a way out.

35
00:13:33.380 --> 00:13:35.041
Some new place.

36
00:13:37.185 --> 00:13:38.447
Or maybe just...

37
00:13:39.054 --> 00:13:40.214
an old one.

38
00:13:40.589 --> 00:13:41.578
Furya.

39
00:13:42.757 --> 00:13:44.486
I know what it's called.

40
00:13:45.594 --> 00:13:47.391
You just don't know where it is.

41
00:13:48.263 --> 00:13:51.062
- I need charts. I need maps.
- Impossible.

42
00:13:51.133 --> 00:13:52.065
I need a direction.

43
00:13:52.168 --> 00:13:54.261
Purged from all records.
as you well know.

44
00:13:54.303 --> 00:13:58.069
But you remember where.
Commander Vaako.

45
00:13:59.775 --> 00:14:01.106
So many worlds...

46
00:14:03.080 --> 00:14:05.776
The only map left in existence...

47
00:14:06.516 --> 00:14:08.416
is the one that's in my head...

48
00:14:09.486 --> 00:14:10.384
Riddick.

49
00:14:16.394 --> 00:14:17.759
So what do you want?

50
00:14:22.066 --> 00:14:23.158
The crown?

51
00:14:28.506 --> 00:14:30.168
Transcendence.

52
00:14:34.647 --> 00:14:35.636
Krone.

53
00:14:36.782 --> 00:14:37.680
Break off a ship.

54
00:14:39.985 --> 00:14:41.213
Riddick's going home.

55
00:14:42.621 --> 00:14:43.611
Vaako.

56
00:14:47.227 --> 00:14:49.695
You can't blame him
for dangling Furya.

57
00:14:51.431 --> 00:14:53.160
Home has a certain equity.

58
00:14:56.670 --> 00:15:00.266
But I do blame him for what came next.

59
00:15:15.490 --> 00:15:17.014
It's a long way to come.

60
00:15:18.126 --> 00:15:19.218
For this.

61
00:15:21.296 --> 00:15:24.198
This guy with
the fucked-up face. Krone...

62
00:15:25.234 --> 00:15:27.099
he was supposed to be our ride home.

63
00:15:30.039 --> 00:15:35.500
But instead of Furya.
we wind up someplace called...

64
00:15:36.112 --> 00:15:37.705
Not Furya.

65
00:15:46.990 --> 00:15:50.016
Yet again.
someone was trying to play me.

66
00:15:52.597 --> 00:15:53.996
So yet again...

67
00:15:56.601 --> 00:15:58.228
we play for blood.

68
00:17:30.468 --> 00:17:32.902
You keep what you kill. Riddick!!

69
00:17:33.972 --> 00:17:35.599
You keep what you kill!

70
00:17:41.914 --> 00:17:44.712
Somewhere along the way.
I lost a step.

71
00:17:45.518 --> 00:17:47.418
I got sloppy.

72
00:17:47.920 --> 00:17:49.683
Dulled my own edge.

73
00:17:51.724 --> 00:17:54.250
Maybe I went and
did the worst crime of all...

74
00:17:56.463 --> 00:17:58.328
I got civilized.

75
00:18:05.539 --> 00:18:08.407
So now we zero the clock.

76
00:18:10.078 --> 00:18:13.479
Just me and this no-name world.

77
00:18:16.317 --> 00:18:18.808
Gotta find that animal side again.

78
00:19:27.860 --> 00:19:28.850
Before long...

79
00:19:29.897 --> 00:19:33.128
I realized there was
a whole other world over there...

80
00:19:34.168 --> 00:19:37.035
of water. grass and life.

81
00:19:39.273 --> 00:19:41.969
Just had one thing in my way.

82
00:23:25.816 --> 00:23:27.647
Come on. show me some teeth.

83
00:24:41.564 --> 00:24:43.156
Escape artist. huh?

84
00:27:26.508 --> 00:27:27.668
What have you got over there?

85
00:27:40.423 --> 00:27:41.890
Thought we shared everything.

86
00:28:05.817 --> 00:28:06.715
Drop it.

87
00:29:05.647 --> 00:29:06.705
Stay.

88
00:29:42.654 --> 00:29:44.121
Bounty hunters...

89
00:29:59.372 --> 00:30:00.134
Wait.

90
00:30:02.675 --> 00:30:03.903
Wait...

91
00:30:04.510 --> 00:30:05.442
Steady...

92
00:30:07.014 --> 00:30:07.776
Okay. now.

93
00:30:14.354 --> 00:30:15.321
Sounds good.

94
00:30:28.136 --> 00:30:29.034
All yours.

95
00:30:35.778 --> 00:30:37.302
It says "dog food" on it.

96
00:30:39.014 --> 00:30:40.413
If you could read.

97
00:30:46.255 --> 00:30:47.187
Come on...

98
00:30:53.430 --> 00:30:55.091
Alright. Bring me my reserve.

99
00:31:09.747 --> 00:31:10.736
Where's yours?

100
00:31:40.780 --> 00:31:41.371
Rain.

101
00:31:42.883 --> 00:31:43.872
It's a good thing.

102
00:31:45.486 --> 00:31:48.546
Just because you've never seen it
before doesn't mean it's a bad thing.

103
00:31:49.923 --> 00:31:51.857
Hey... easy...

104
00:32:06.508 --> 00:32:08.601
Looks like our time is up here.

105
00:34:07.771 --> 00:34:08.362
Nothing.

106
00:34:11.476 --> 00:34:12.465
Look again. Diaz.

107
00:34:16.948 --> 00:34:19.143
Somebody should teach
this Riddick asshole how to count.

108
00:34:20.218 --> 00:34:21.378
"Leave one ship"?

109
00:34:22.387 --> 00:34:24.218
Like we've got a fucking spare
laying around.

110
00:34:25.224 --> 00:34:26.555
Let's crank it up.

111
00:34:37.670 --> 00:34:39.468
Morning. Cyclps.

112
00:35:03.664 --> 00:35:04.358
Hey. Luna.

113
00:35:07.636 --> 00:35:08.227
Yeah.

114
00:35:09.404 --> 00:35:10.996
Wake her up. kick her outta bed.

115
00:35:11.640 --> 00:35:12.504
What do you mean?

116
00:35:13.475 --> 00:35:14.407
We're running heavy.

117
00:35:15.277 --> 00:35:15.902
She's a prisoner.

118
00:35:16.111 --> 00:35:18.079
- Wasn't she gonna pay our way back?
- We're going big now.

119
00:35:18.947 --> 00:35:22.440
Okay? Cut that 60 kilos loose.

120
00:35:38.702 --> 00:35:42.035
- Get away! Get away from me!
- Stop. just stop!

121
00:35:42.206 --> 00:35:43.298
What do you want now?

122
00:35:43.640 --> 00:35:46.268
I'm gonna take off the restraints.
Okay?

123
00:35:48.279 --> 00:35:50.770
- I don't want them off.
- No. it's not like that.

124
00:35:51.883 --> 00:35:53.214
Nobody's gonna touch you now.

125
00:35:53.785 --> 00:35:55.582
Santana's head is into other stuff now.

126
00:35:57.288 --> 00:35:58.050
Your lucky day.

127
00:36:05.364 --> 00:36:06.763
- Get the fuck away from me.
- Alright.

128
00:36:09.602 --> 00:36:11.593
What planet is this?
Where are we?

129
00:36:11.670 --> 00:36:13.467
It's got air and water.
That's all you gotta know.

130
00:36:18.011 --> 00:36:19.911
- But how am I supposed to survive?
- Just go.

131
00:36:21.381 --> 00:36:23.008
Before he changes his mind.

132
00:36:48.844 --> 00:36:50.641
I was getting attached to her.

133
00:36:53.849 --> 00:36:55.750
Now where is my box at?

134
00:37:18.709 --> 00:37:19.505
The name...

135
00:37:20.411 --> 00:37:21.845
is Santana!

136
00:37:23.048 --> 00:37:25.744
Shot-caller for this crew right here!

137
00:37:27.052 --> 00:37:32.752
I am the guy who knows all.
sees all. beats all!

138
00:37:33.925 --> 00:37:35.689
Spitting it kinda strong. ain't he?

139
00:37:37.497 --> 00:37:38.794
Gotta bait the trap.

140
00:37:39.699 --> 00:37:43.999
I've come all this way
to collect your head in a box!

141
00:37:44.070 --> 00:37:45.298
Right here!

142
00:37:46.973 --> 00:37:49.204
So have yourself a fine day now...

143
00:37:49.510 --> 00:37:51.569
Mr. Richard B. Riddick!

144
00:37:52.446 --> 00:37:53.936
I suspect...

145
00:37:55.015 --> 00:37:58.951
it will be one...
of your very last!

146
00:37:59.786 --> 00:38:03.814
Well. you don't need to agitate Riddick
any more than... you know.

147
00:38:05.360 --> 00:38:07.590
Any more than bringing his head
back in a box would?

148
00:38:33.924 --> 00:38:35.050
Shit.

149
00:38:35.992 --> 00:38:37.653
Here comes the neighborhood.

150
00:38:43.066 --> 00:38:43.931
Small world.

151
00:38:52.843 --> 00:38:56.837
Unidentified vessel.
this is Clan Vagos out of Ursa Five.

152
00:38:57.049 --> 00:38:59.040
Be advised that
we are on the ground now

153
00:38:59.151 --> 00:39:01.381
and have responded
to emergency signal.

154
00:39:01.653 --> 00:39:05.180
No distress found. no need to land.

155
00:39:05.824 --> 00:39:10.319
I repeat. there is no reason for you
to land at this location at this time.

156
00:39:10.897 --> 00:39:12.125
Is that clear?

157
00:39:12.265 --> 00:39:16.292
No reason for you to land
at this location at this time.

158
00:39:18.805 --> 00:39:20.500
What the fuck did I just say?!

159
00:39:38.660 --> 00:39:40.992
It was a long haul.
We could take on some water.

160
00:39:42.197 --> 00:39:44.028
Wouldn't mind a little
true-gravity time either.

161
00:39:45.133 --> 00:39:48.034
Like I was saying. I've got this.

162
00:39:54.910 --> 00:39:57.970
You know who that was. right?
On the emergency beacon?

163
00:40:00.783 --> 00:40:02.648
Wouldn't be here if I didn't.

164
00:40:04.020 --> 00:40:06.512
The concept of back-up still
has no appeal to you?

165
00:40:07.257 --> 00:40:09.987
My besties here can ball with anyone.

166
00:40:10.360 --> 00:40:12.828
No disrespect for your crew.
of course.

167
00:40:13.397 --> 00:40:17.128
who look strong. too.
in those matchy-matchy outfits.

168
00:40:17.301 --> 00:40:19.827
Shit. Didn't know
there was a dress code.

169
00:40:20.204 --> 00:40:21.228
Yeah. right?

170
00:40:21.606 --> 00:40:23.972
Well. it's not my intention
to jump another man's claim.

171
00:40:25.310 --> 00:40:27.744
If you don't mind. maybe we'll just pull
up a chair and spectate for a while.

172
00:40:30.248 --> 00:40:31.237
What if I do?

173
00:40:32.318 --> 00:40:35.014
This is a Co-op station. pal.
It's open to all mercs.

174
00:40:37.022 --> 00:40:39.388
- By the way. my name is...
- "Too late".

175
00:40:39.792 --> 00:40:42.852
That's your name.
Too Late.

176
00:40:43.662 --> 00:40:46.393
And I don't need you stepping
all over my dick here. my friend.

177
00:40:47.400 --> 00:40:48.389
Well. I tell you what.

178
00:40:50.170 --> 00:40:52.798
I won't lift a finger to help you until
you come ask me for it. How's that?

179
00:41:11.325 --> 00:41:14.591
I was scoping this out earlier.
It's a cave system. Five clicks south.

180
00:41:16.031 --> 00:41:16.998
Might be worth a look.

181
00:41:18.667 --> 00:41:19.759
Hey. Too Late.

182
00:41:20.736 --> 00:41:24.103
Need to pull a node from your ship and
store it right here next to mine. Okay?

183
00:41:24.506 --> 00:41:25.404
Oh. really? Why's that?

184
00:41:25.974 --> 00:41:28.500
Riddick triggered the beacon
to get off-world. right?

185
00:41:29.879 --> 00:41:33.906
Basically. he was calling a taxi.

186
00:41:35.952 --> 00:41:36.475
And...?

187
00:41:37.553 --> 00:41:39.749
And a ship would make
a sweet trap. right?

188
00:41:40.391 --> 00:41:44.418
Confined space. metal walls...
jail cell.

189
00:41:45.796 --> 00:41:46.820
Ace cool. huh?

190
00:41:47.297 --> 00:41:50.630
Is it true half the people you meet
are below average intelligence?

191
00:41:50.667 --> 00:41:53.535
Got to make sure the ship stays grounded
when he comes for them. okay?

192
00:41:54.406 --> 00:41:54.895
Come on.

193
00:41:55.640 --> 00:41:58.473
Dahl... pull a node from the ship.

194
00:42:23.804 --> 00:42:24.236
I'll do it!

195
00:42:45.927 --> 00:42:47.485
Any time now. Riddick.

196
00:43:11.721 --> 00:43:15.783
I'm telling you. this is total overkill.
Eleven of us out here now?

197
00:43:16.193 --> 00:43:18.627
Should have been a four-man op. tops.

198
00:43:18.929 --> 00:43:21.727
You are jinxing our janx. man.
And that ain't cool.

199
00:43:21.932 --> 00:43:25.095
Hey. I don't give a shit what they say.
He's one guy.

200
00:43:27.605 --> 00:43:28.937
Whatever you say.

201
00:43:30.242 --> 00:43:31.334
He's one guy.

202
00:43:47.093 --> 00:43:50.028
So I guess that's what passes for
a fucking moon on this planet.

203
00:43:51.397 --> 00:43:52.830
It's gonna be a dark night.

204
00:43:54.000 --> 00:43:55.228
Advantage. him.

205
00:43:56.937 --> 00:44:00.532
Maybe he's gonna wear you down first.
Force you to go without sleep.

206
00:44:00.974 --> 00:44:02.635
Can't you see I'm busy?

207
00:44:03.844 --> 00:44:05.505
I'm just sharing my thoughts.

208
00:44:06.046 --> 00:44:08.810
Well. now that you have...

209
00:44:10.518 --> 00:44:15.353
can I politely invite you to
step off my fucking porch?!

210
00:44:17.959 --> 00:44:19.153
I'll start rotating down.

211
00:44:19.861 --> 00:44:20.725
You let me know. huh?

212
00:44:21.329 --> 00:44:24.060
As soon as I have his head in a box.
I will let you know.

213
00:44:49.459 --> 00:44:51.451
Grid 29D.
Stand by. stand by.

214
00:44:56.901 --> 00:44:57.765
What you got. cuz?

215
00:45:01.172 --> 00:45:02.833
Some dingo-dongo thing.

216
00:45:07.512 --> 00:45:09.742
Yeah. I see it now.

217
00:45:10.415 --> 00:45:11.382
You want me to pop it?

218
00:45:11.650 --> 00:45:13.845
Knock it down.
One shot suppressed.

219
00:45:19.258 --> 00:45:21.692
Nice work. Diaz.
Encouraging.

220
00:45:22.729 --> 00:45:23.821
Had something in my eye.

221
00:45:24.364 --> 00:45:25.558
It's called a scope.

222
00:45:26.466 --> 00:45:27.524
Try next time.

223
00:45:28.301 --> 00:45:29.290
You got this. right?

224
00:45:31.238 --> 00:45:33.263
Will you get off my freaking frequency!

225
00:45:57.933 --> 00:45:59.059
What the fuck is going on here?

226
00:46:21.425 --> 00:46:22.983
Thank fucking God!

227
00:46:24.027 --> 00:46:25.120
Fuck off!

228
00:46:28.132 --> 00:46:32.091
Rubio. coming your way now.
Gotta swap out a bad sensor.

229
00:46:36.107 --> 00:46:37.665
What was here versus what was found.

230
00:46:38.944 --> 00:46:40.036
How does it square?

231
00:46:40.679 --> 00:46:44.012
Pretty good. The morphine's gone.
but that's always the first thing to go.

232
00:46:46.018 --> 00:46:47.485
That was a bit weird. though.

233
00:46:48.987 --> 00:46:51.979
"A predator restraint
with 4 2-inch offset jaws."

234
00:46:52.592 --> 00:46:54.651
Six listed. zero found.

235
00:46:55.462 --> 00:46:57.555
Well. it is an odd thing
to go for a walk.

236
00:46:58.131 --> 00:47:01.066
Yeah. but Boss. you know how
shit goes missing from these stations.

237
00:47:01.101 --> 00:47:03.467
One bad year and guys
are ripping shit off for salvage.

238
00:47:12.613 --> 00:47:13.602
Hey. Santana?

239
00:47:14.849 --> 00:47:17.215
You did sweep the area
before I got here. right?

240
00:47:17.618 --> 00:47:18.778
Sweep for what?

241
00:47:19.688 --> 00:47:21.883
Well. I just want to make sure
no one has set any traps for us.

242
00:47:22.157 --> 00:47:23.146
5Q.

243
00:47:26.061 --> 00:47:28.757
- Understand what I'm saying?
- Traps?

244
00:47:29.131 --> 00:47:30.189
What kind of traps?

245
00:47:30.632 --> 00:47:32.065
The kind with jaws.

246
00:47:39.342 --> 00:47:40.900
Don't touch that fucking thing!

247
00:47:47.451 --> 00:47:48.315
What?

248
00:47:52.956 --> 00:47:53.718
Up-armor.

249
00:48:04.369 --> 00:48:04.960
Shit!

250
00:48:06.004 --> 00:48:06.732
Ready. ready.

251
00:48:11.075 --> 00:48:13.168
Stay put. stay put!
Stay put. stay put!

252
00:48:23.155 --> 00:48:24.952
Who the hell was
that screaming and why?

253
00:48:27.360 --> 00:48:28.088
Nunez...

254
00:48:29.329 --> 00:48:30.694
break out the sweep gear.

255
00:48:31.798 --> 00:48:35.131
And figure out how many
of these big-ass traps...

256
00:48:35.202 --> 00:48:36.829
we got out here. okay?

257
00:48:38.538 --> 00:48:43.033
I'm thinking maybe the whole upper left
quad is some kind of fucking mine field.

258
00:48:43.945 --> 00:48:45.537
You do that now. okay. Nunez?

259
00:48:48.015 --> 00:48:49.448
Copy that. Nunez?

260
00:48:54.288 --> 00:48:55.449
Nunez?

261
00:48:57.993 --> 00:49:00.461
This is bad.
This is very bad.

262
00:49:02.598 --> 00:49:05.294
